---
/*
  Equal Opportunities (EDI) and Disability Confident guidance for applicants.
*/
---
<!-- EDI SECTION -->
<section class="mb-10">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Equality, Diversity & Inclusion (EDI)</h2>

  <p>
    Green Orbit Digital is committed to fostering an inclusive, supportive, and equitable workplace.  
    We value diversity of backgrounds, perspectives, and lived experiences across all areas of the business.
    Our recruitment processes ensure fair treatment for all candidates regardless of age, disability,
    neurodivergence, gender reassignment, marriage and civil partnership, pregnancy and maternity, race,
    religion or belief, sex, or sexual orientation.
  </p>

  <p class="mt-2">
    We continually review our policies, processes, and working culture to ensure accessibility and inclusion
    across the full employee journey â€” from recruitment to progression.
  </p>

  <!-- Link Button -->
  <a 
    href="/recruitment/equal-opportunities"
    class="inline-block mt-4 px-5 py-3 rounded bg-accent-600 text-white font-semibold hover:bg-accent-700 transition"
  >
    View Our EDI & Equal Opportunities Policy
  </a>
</section>


<!-- DISABILITY CONFIDENT SECTION -->
<section class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start gap-6 mb-6">

  <!-- Logo -->
  <img 
    src="/logos/pledges/disability-confident.png" 
    alt="Disability Confident Logo"
    class="w-24 md:w-32 lg:w-40 max-w-full h-auto flex-shrink-0"
  />

  <div>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Disability Confident & Accessible Recruitment</h2>

    <p>
      We proudly support the Disability Confident Committed pledge and ensure our recruitment and working
      practices are accessible to disabled and neurodivergent applicants. If you require reasonable
      adjustments at any stage, you can request them during your application or by 
      <a href="/contact" class="underline text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-300">contacting us</a>
      directly.
    </p>
    <p>
      If invited to interview, you may request to be considered under the Disability Confident Scheme.
      To qualify, applicants must meet all essential criteria listed for the role.
    </p>
  </div>

</section>